==Russian==

===Noun===
'''ру́сский''' (rússkij) {{m}}, русская (rússkaja) {{f}}, русские (rússkije) {{p}}

# [[Russian]], an ethnic Russian person (for other ethnicities living in Russia, see [[россиянин]])
#: ты что, не русский? — ''You’re Russian, aren’t you?''
# {{colloquial}} the Russian [[language]]
#: ты знаешь русский? — ''Do you know Russian?''

====Usage notes====
Do not confuse the noun or adjective [[русский]] with [[российский]]/[[россиянин]], all of which translate to [[Russian]].
:The word [[русский]], concerning a person or people, means pertaining to ethnic East Slavic [[Russians]] only, but not other ethnic groups in Russia.
:The word [[российский]] means pertaining to the [[state]] or [[nation]] of Russia.

